      <span class='time published'><a href="#2003-12-16T09:56:00Z" name="2003-12-16T09:56:00Z"><abbr class="dtstart" title="2003-12-16T09:56:00Z">9.56 am</abbr></a></span>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0415P1_20031216_WH_15'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-annabelle-ewing' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0415P1_20031216_WH_15' title='Link to this speech by Ms Annabelle Ewing' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-annabelle-ewing" title="Ms Annabelle Ewing">Annabelle Ewing</a></cite>
          <span class='member_constituency'><a href="/constituencies/perth-1" title="Perth">(Perth) (SNP)</a></span>
          <p class='first-para'>
            Thank you, Sir Nicholas. I am pleased to be called to speak in this debate. I congratulate the hon. Member for Orkney and Shetland (Mr. Carmichael) on securing this extremely important debate, which neither the UK Government in London nor the Government in Edinburgh appear to want to have in their own time&#x2014;at least, not to date. I am not entirely sure whether I am required to declare an interest, but I am a qualified Scots lawyer and, hence, a member of the Law Society of Scotland.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0415P1_20031216_WH_16'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-alistair-carmichael' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0415P1_20031216_WH_16' title='Link to this speech by Mr Alistair Carmichael' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
